# Issue #157 proof corpus — hand-authored witnesses for the experimental
# query-context functions start()/end()/step()/range() (grammar patch G4
# + plan-time constant folding). Semantics ported from Prometheus v3.13.0
# @ 40af9c2: the four calls fold to NumberLiterals in PreprocessExpr
# (engine.go:4436-4481 foldQueryContextFunctions) — start() = query start
# seconds, end() = query end seconds, range() = end - start, and step() =
# 0 when start == end, else step seconds. Instant queries preprocess with
# (ts, ts, 0) (engine.go:558), so all four are the instant timestamp /
# zero there. The values are query-window constants: identical at every
# step of a range query (the step-invariance upstream folds to obtain,
# which PulsusDB gets from PlanExpr::Scalar).
#
# The corpus-gated home for the upstream rows is functions.test (oracle
# lines 2053-2189), skip-manifested until its activation issue (#163);
# this file is the manifest-witness path in the meantime.

# --- Bare instant calls (start == end == ts; range and step are 0). ---

eval instant at 100s start()
	100

eval instant at 100s end()
	100

eval instant at 100s step()
	0

eval instant at 100s range()
	0

# --- Bare range calls: query-window constants at every step. ---

eval range from 0 to 30s step 10s start()
	{} 0 0 0 0

eval range from 0 to 30s step 10s end()
	{} 30 30 30 30

eval range from 0 to 10s step 5s step()
	{} 5 5 5

eval range from 0 to 30s step 10s range()
	{} 30 30 30 30

# --- Nonzero-`from` ranges: start()/end()/range() are query boundaries,
# --- never evaluation timestamps.

eval range from 100s to 130s step 10s start()
	{} 100 100 100 100

eval range from 100s to 130s step 10s end()
	{} 130 130 130 130

eval range from 10s to 50s step 10s range()
	{} 40 40 40 40 40

# --- Compositions (scalar arithmetic over the folded constants). ---

eval range from 10s to 20s step 5s end() - start()
	{} 10 10 10

eval range from 0s to 20s step 10s start() + range()
	{} 20 20 20

eval range from 0s to 30s step 10s (end() + start()) / 2
	{} 15 15 15 15

# --- vector() wrapping. ---

eval range from 0 to 10s step 5s vector(step())
	{} 5 5 5

# --- Load-backed arithmetic: a real fetch multiplied by the constant. ---

load 1s
	metric 1 2 3 4 5

eval range from 0s to 4s step 1s metric * step()
	{} 1 2 3 4 5
